  <!--
    🚫 Arcade / MAME — openemu.system.arcade
    The Arcade system plugin (UI layer) exists at OpenEmu/SystemPlugins/Arcade/ and is fully
    configured with controller mappings, file types (.zip, .7z, .chd, .bin, .rom), and 8-player
    support. However, there is NO MAME emulation core in this project.

    This is why users see a greyed-out Arcade entry in Settings → Cores with nothing to select.

    A MAME core would need to:
      - Subclass OEGameCore and implement OEArcadeSystemResponderClient
      - Compile MAME (modern versions support ARM64/AArch64 natively)
      - Register here under openemu.system.arcade

    Tracking issue: https://github.com/chris-p-bacon-sudo/openemu-silicon/issues/25
  -->

  <!--
    The following cores are x86_64 only in the official OpenEmu releases.
    They require ARM64 builds to be hosted before they can be re-enabled here.
    Tracking issue: https://github.com/bazley82/OpenEmuARM64/issues

    Excluded cores:
      BSNES        — Super Nintendo (accuracy)
      DeSmuME      — Nintendo DS
      Mednafen     — PSX, Saturn, Lynx, WonderSwan, PC Engine, Neo Geo Pocket
      Stella       — Atari 2600
      Atari800     — Atari 5200
      O2EM         — Odyssey2/Videopac
      Picodrive    — Sega 32X
      Mupen64Plus  — Nintendo 64
      Bliss        — Intellivision
      VecXGL       — Vectrex
      CrabEmu      — ColecoVision / Sega Master System
  -->

</cores>
